@node "PolEdMS" "Picture Dictionary Drill - Edit Fields"

  @{b}Picture Dictionary Drill - Edit Fields@{ub}

  There are few Editing Fields in Multiple Choice Drills.  Click on one of them to get
more information:

   @{" Question      " link "Question1" 0}
   @{" Question File " link "SoundFile" 0}
   @{" Picture File  " link "PictureFile" 0}
   @{" Answers       " link "Answers" 0}
   @{" Answer Files  " link "SoundFile" 0}
@endnode

@node "PolEdMT" "Picture Multiple Choice - Edit Fields"

  @{b}Picture Multiple Choice - Edit Fields@{ub}

 In Picture Multiple Choice exercises, there are three different fields to fill in:

   @{" Picture File " link "PictureFile" 0}
   @{" Answers      " link "Answers" 0}
   @{" Answer Files " link "SoundFile" 0}
@endnode

@node "Kodowanie" "Special Answer Coding"

  @{b}Special Answer Coding@{ub}

  In each answer field you can code several answers using special coding. Using this
technique allows you to define a template of correct answers.

  In coding answers you may use three characters @{b}[ / ]@{ub} (brackets and forward slash).
You should use @{b}[]@{ub} (brackets) only for coding purposes.

 @{b}@{u}Coding rules@{ub}@{uu}

   A.  Optional parts

       If part of the text is placed between @{b}brackets@{ub} ( [ and ] )
       it means that the component is optional.  For example:

@{b}           He said [that] he was ill.@{ub}

      means that two different answers will be accepted:

            1. He said that he was ill.
            2. He said he was ill.


   B.  Alternative parts

       If there is a / (slash) character between brackets
       ([ and ], it means that any one of the parts listed between
       the brackets is is acceptable as part of the answer. At least ONE
       of these answers is required. Each valid part is separated by a
       slash.

       Example:

                We['ll/ shall/ will] overcome.

      means that user can type 'll OR shall OR will.  There are three
      acceptable answers:

            1. We'll overcome
            2. We shall overcome.
            3. We will overcome.


      note the "'ll" in the example above - it's written WITHOUT a
      leading space! "Shall" and "will" have to be specified with
      leading spaces because a sentence like "Wewill overcome" is
      definitely wrong.

      You can also use more than one slash (/) in a coded answer.

  C.  Mixing A and B elements

      You can mix both forms of coding and you can put each of them into
      embedded sequences.  For example:

            I [do[n't/ not] have/have[n't/ not][ got]] a car.


      givs six acceptable answers:

         1. I have not a car.
         2. I do not have a car.
         3. I don't have a car.
         4. I haven't a car.
         5. I have not got a car.
         6. I haven't got a car.



  You can code several answers into one field but sometimes it is difficult to create a
good matching pattern. Don't overcomplicate the coding until you get used to it.

  NOTE: Do not use coding if you are not sure your 'template' accepts only
        good answers. It's easy to make a hard-to-track bug in a coded
        answer, so think twice before you use this feature!

  When you give an answer eTeacher "decompresses" all coded answers and compares them
to your given answer.  When your answer compares correctly it is printed on the screen
as a correct answer.  If your answer doesn't match any of them, eTeacher prints the
FIRST correct answer.  Remember to put the MOST correct answer at the top of the answer
list.

@endnode

@node "Question1" "Question"

  @{b}Question@{ub}

 In this field you have to supply a question.  Usually it's a phrase with empty spaces
to fill in with a given word or expression.  In the empty space simply write a few (we
suggest 4) "____" (underscore) characters.

 NOTE: the number of underscores used makes no difference to eTeacher.
       It's just a visual indication to the user that something should
       be placed there. It is advisable to always use the same number
       of underscores (4 suggested) in order to discourage the user from
       guessing the correct answer based on the number of underscores.

       e.g., put "____" if you want user to answer "a" and put "____" if
       you want him/her to type "incredible".


Your answer will replace the empty place.  When you use more than one empty space in a
question, answers should be separated by a comma followed by a space (", ").
@endnode

@node "Question2" "Question"

  @{b}Question@{ub}

  This field must be filled in with a question.  It can be a word, a phrase to
translate, a phrase with empty spaces to fill, or a phrase to be transformed. In each
exercise you have to fill in the header.

Don't forget to give simple instruction for each exercise.
@endnode

@node "PictureFile" "Picture File"

  @{b}Picture File@{ub}

  All picture names are inserted automaticaly from a file requester.  You can use IFF
saved image files, fixed at a size of 128x128 pixel each.

  Remember - older Amigas (ECS/OCS) can only use 16 colours in HiRes modes, (AGA or
graphics card can use up to 256 colors per image), so either prepare two sets of
exercises (with 16 colour images and 256 colour images) or else use only 16-colour
images so that all Amigas can use them.

  The displayed image will be automatically adapted to match the current screen palette
and available colours, but it you want to remap your images yourself, see the contents
of the "Support" drawer. We put optimised pallette files here, so you can load it into
your favourite image processing software and render your images using these colours.

  If using your own palette, remember that AmigaOS locks 8 colours (0, 1, 2, 3 and the
4 last colours) on each screen for its own purposes (gadgets, window borders etc). And
don't forget that the mouse pointer also has definable colours, so make sure your
palette won't make the pointer disappear.
@endnode

@node "SoundFile" "Sound File"

  @{b}Sound File@{ub}

  File names are inserted automatically from a file requester.  At the right side of
each sound file gadget are placed two different gadgets:

   1.to open file reqester
   2.to play the sample (see @{" Sound Options " link "OptionsSND" 0} for more infomation)

  eTeachers can internally (INTERNAL) read and play sound files stored in the following
formats:

    - IFF 8SVX
    - WAVE  8 bit mono
    - WAVE 16 bit mono

All 16 bit samples are converted to 8 bits while replaying on 8 bit audio hardware
(e.g. the built-in Paula chip). Sound card owners will hear full 16 bit audio.

  When using an EXTERNAL sample player you can use all formats that your favourite
external player supports. We suggest that you try Play16 to get 14 bit Paula sound from
16 bit WAVE files.

  Under AmigaOS 3 (or later) equipped Amigas, the datatype system can be utilised to
play ANY sample that datatypes can read.

  AHI users: there's special patch for sound.datatype to make it use
             your audio card. Please see the "Support" drawer.


  As with any other modern software, eTeacher can utilise the AHI audio system. At
least version 4 of the AHI system is required. Using it you can play IFF and WAVE 8 and
16 bit mono samples on your 16 bit audio card as well as on the Amiga's Paula chip.

  Please see the contents of the "Support" drawer on this CD to get the latest versions
of AHI, Play16, sound datatypes and other useful tools and system expansions.
@endnode

@node "WykCwiczen" "Working with execises"

  @{b}Working with execises@{ub}

  All exercises have a number of items to learn.  You give the answer for the displayed
question, fill in the sequence, translate somethig, etc. In Multiple Choice drills you
simply have to click on the correct answer.  In other exercise types you have to enter
the answer on the keyboard.

   In @{" Learn Mode " link "Learn" 0} all items are repeated until all
      are answered correctly.

   In @{" Test Mode  " link "Test" 0} each item appears only once.  At the
      end of drill you'll get scored based on how many correct answers
      were given.

   To get the next item simply click on the big arrow gadget or press
   ENTER.

  In all exercises internal grammar help is available.  You can abort the current
exercise by pressing "Cancel".  All exercises have hints on how to make them correct -
click on the "Instruction" gadget to see the instruction text again at any time.

 If you want to know how to learn in a choosen exercise type, please see
@{" Exercise Types " link "TypyCW" 0}.

  While working with the exercise you can pause it at any time by clicking on the
"Pause" gadget. The timer will stop and an information window will appear. To get back
to the exercise, confirm this requester by clicking on the "Ok" button.
@endnode

@node "TypyCW" "Exercise types"

  @{b}Exercise types@{ub}

 eTeacher offers nine types of exercises.  Click on the type of interest to get more
information:

   @{" Multiple Choice Questions  " link "TW" 0}
   @{" Picture Multiple Choices   " link "MTW" 0}
   @{" Dictionary Drill           " link "SL" 0}
   @{" Picture Dictionary Drill   " link "MSL" 0}
   @{" Filling Blanks             " link "SL" 0}
   @{" Phrase Transformation      " link "TRA" 0}
   @{" Fixed Words Transformation " link "TRA" 0}
   @{" Question Formation         " link "TRA" 0}
   @{" Translation of Phrases     " link "SL" 0}
@endnode

@node "Learn" "Learn Mode"

  @{b}Learn Mode@{ub}

 In Learn Mode eTeacher ask you for an answer.  When you give an incorrect answer
eTeacher will ask the same question later on.  In Teaching Options there is a special
slider to set learn @{" Intensity level " link "IntLEVEL" 0}. When this value is greater than 1 you'll have to
give a correct answer more than 1 time to get credit for it (for example,  intensity=3
means that eTeacher will require three correct answers for the current item in the
drill to tell you that "you have learned this item").  Default intensity is 1.

  Grammar help is available in grammar exercises.  You can also use the @{" AutoRepeat " link "ARepeat" 0}
option.  When this flag is set to TRUE, eTeacher will repeat the question until a
correct answer is given. You must give the correct answer to proceed to the next step.
When the flag @{" Credit after Auto Repeat " link "AutoRCredit" 0} is set, you will be given credit for such
"corrected" answers.
@endnode

@node "Test" "Test Mode"

  @{b}Test Mode@{ub}

  In Test Mode eTeacher asks each item only once (it doesn't matter if the answer was
correct or not).  During the test, eTeacher tracks the percentage of good answers and
scores you at the end of the test. The scale is different for each exercise.

   In @{" Teaching Options " link "OptionsTEA" 0} you can change the strictness of the program and whether or
not the grammar help should be available during the test.
@endnode

@node "TW" "Multiple Choice Drill"

  @{b}Multiple Choice Drill@{ub}

 In this kind of drill you have to select the correct answer from those listed. Choose
theme to get more information.

   @{" Working with exercises     " link "WykCwiczen" 0}
   @{" Buttons                    " link "Przyciski" 0}
   @{" Choosing answers           " link "WyborOdpTW" 0}
   @{" Informations on the screen " link "ScreenInfo" 0}

 In Multiple Choice exercises only ONE answer is correct!

 Exercise files have MLT extension.
@endnode

@node "MTW" "Picture Multiple Choice"

  @{b}Picture Multiple Choice@{ub}

  In this kind of exercise you click on the picture corresponding to the correct
answer. Choose theme to get more information.

  @{" Working with exercises     " link "WykCwiczen" 0}
  @{" Buttons                    " link "Przyciski" 0}
  @{" Choosing answers           " link "WyborOdpTW" 0}
  @{" Informations on the screen " link "ScreenInfo" 0}

 In Picture Multiple Choice exercises only ONE answer is correct!

 Exercise files have MPD extension.
@endnode

@node "SL" "Dictionary Drill"

  @{b}Dictionary Drill@{ub}

  In these exercise you must enter the correct answer exactly - please read the
instruction for each file.  Choose theme to get more information.

  @{" Working with exercises     " link "WykCwiczen" 0}
  @{" Buttons                    " link "Przyciski" 0}
  @{" Typing answers             " link "Answers" 0}
  @{" Informations on the screen " link "ScreenInfo" 0}

 Exercise files have DIC, DEP, TRA or FIL extension.
@endnode

@node "MSL" "Picture Dictionary Drill"

  @{b}Picture Dictionary Drill@{ub}

  In this kind of exercise you must enter the word describing an object shown in a
picture.  Choose theme to get more information:

  @{" Working with exercises     " link "WykCwiczen" 0}
  @{" Buttons                    " link "Przyciski" 0}
  @{" Typing answers             " link "Answers" 0}
  @{" Informations on the screen " link "ScreenInfo" 0}

 Exercise files have WPD extensions.
@endnode

@node "TRA" "Transforamtion Drill"

  @{b}Transforamtion Drill@{ub}

  In these exercises you must carefully enter the answer using elements from the
Component Name window.  Choose the theme for more information:

   @{" Working with exercises     " link "WykCwiczen" 0}
   @{" Buttons                    " link "Przyciski" 0}
   @{" Typing answers             " link "Answers" 0}
   @{" Informations on the screen " link "ScreenInfo" 0}

 Exercise files have PHR, FIX or QUE extensions.
@endnode

@node "Help" "Help"

  @{b}Help!!!!@{ub}

 Can you help me???

 Just kidding, but I guess you already know what help is for ... ;-)
@endnode

@node "AnswersTW" "Answers in Multiple Choice."

  @{b}Answers in Multiple Choice.@{ub}

  In these fields you should type two to five answers for the user to choose from.

It is recommended that the same number of answers be used consistently in all questions
of the exercise, as scoring is thus simplified, based on the number you use to indicate
the correct "minimum %" in @{" Header Edit " link "HeaderEdit" 0}. Indicate the correct answer by setting the
appropriate radio button.
@endnode

@node "Answers" "Answers"

  @{b}Answers@{ub}

  In these fields you enter all the correct answers.  You can use up to 64 uncoded
answers or use @{" Answer Coding " link "Kodowanie" 0} to increase the possible number of correct answers. Each
answer may have its own sound sample.

  Coded answers can have only one sound sample, so if you want more, you cannot use the
coding feature.
@endnode

@node "Options" "Options"

  @{b}Options@{ub}

 In the Options menu you can change the program parameters.  The menu contains the
following options:

   @{" Program options  " link "OptionsPRG" 0}
   @{" Teaching options " link "OptionsTEA" 0}
   @{" Sound            " link "OptionsSND" 0}
   @{" Graphics         " link "OptionsGFX" 0}
   @{" Comments         " link "OptionsCOM" 0}
   @{" Workbench        " link "OptionsWB" 0}
   @{" Save Settings    " link "OptionsSVE" 0}
   @{" Default Settings " link "OptionsDefault" 0}
@endnode

@node "OptionsWB" "Workbench"

    @{b}Workbench@{ub}

If your computer has little available memory, you can use this option to close the
Workbench screen (if possible) which frees a few bytes of memory. If "Workbench" is
checked, then the WB screen remains open.

@endnode

@node "OptionsGFX" "Graphics"

 @{b}Graphics options@{ub}

 In this panel you can adjust the following options:

   1. Background Picture
   2. ScreenMode
   3. Miscellaneous

Background

   Here you can specify what you would like to see as the background
   picture in the program's main window. You can choose between:

   a) Default - the defualt background image
   b) None    - select this if you don't care for a background image
   c) One     - one background image, specified by you
   d) Random  - randomly chosen image, changes on every program startup.

ScreenMode

   Here you can specify the screen mode you wish to be used by Electronic
   Teacher. If you force eTeacher to be opened on another public screen,
   this option will be disabled. Save Settings automatically puts the
   necessary information into the program icons.

   If you use a graphics card, we strongly recommend 8-bit screen modes,
   at least 640x400 pixels (or better, like 800x600) in size. Most
   backround images are 720x480 or 768x512.

Miscellaneous

   Various graphics related options.

   If "Try multicolor first" is turned on, eTeacher will always try to open the image
   with with highest available depth.  Normally eTeacher looks for e.g. "CAT.IFF", it
   will first try "CAT.IFF256", then "CAT.IFF128", and down to "CAT.IFF16". If no
   multicolor picture is found it will use "CAT.IFF".

   If "Set pointer colours" is turned on, eTeacher will automatically set colours of
   the mouse pointer. Option DON'T working with depth=5 (32 colours)

   If "Set cursor colours" option is turned on, eTeacher will automatically set cursor
   colours.

   If "Show background info" option is turned on, eTeacher will show background picture
descriptions.
@endnode

@node "OptionsSTAT" "Statistics"

  @{b}Statistics@{ub}

  In the Statistics window you can check which exercises were done, when they were
done, and the scores posted for the excercise. All this information is collected for
all users in separate files. By default, the program displays statistics for the
highlighted (current) user, but if you want to see the results for your friends or
children, please select the name of other students.

If you think the history list is already too long, or holds information you no longer
care about and want to clear your log, just remove yourself in the @{"Users" link "OptionsSTUD" 0} menu and then
create a new user with the same name again (we plan to add "Delete" button to this
window in future releases to simplify this operation).

@endnode

@node "OptionsSTUD" "Users"

  @{b}Students@{ub}

  With eTeacher you can teach yourself alone or together with your friends and
relatives.  In the Users window you can choose to remove and add students who are going
to use the program.  The program collects all student related notes in separate files,
and allows you to to see the results at any time. Just try @{" Statistic Option " link "OptionsSTAT" 0}.

  There is a special flag labeled "Show at startup".  When this flag is set, eTeacher
will ask for the student's name each time you run it.  If you are the only student, you
can turn this feature off.

@endnode

@node "OptionsLAST" "Last used drills"
 This window displays all the drills you recently accessed. The list shows the mode you
accessed the file in:

  @{b}L@{ub} - via Learn menu
  @{b}T@{ub} - via Test menu
  @{b}E@{ub} - via Edit menu
  @{b}C@{ub} - via Create menu

It also shows the file name and description of the drill. You can access drills again
by selecting the desired drill on the list and clicking the proper gadget, depending on
what mode you want use. Please note that you can't "Create" the drill again. You can
only edit it. By using the "Delete" gadget you can remove the selected item from the
list. This DOES NOT affect the file itself. It still remains on the disk and is still
available for further use.

@endnode

@node "OptionsPRG" "Program Options"

  @{b}Program Options@{ub}

 In Program Options you can change these options:

   @{" Program Language " link "PrgLAN" 0}
   @{" Protect          " link "PrgPASW" 0}
   @{" Export           " link "PrgEXP" 0}
   @{" Keyboard         " link "PrgKEY" 0}
@endnode

@node "PrgKEY" "Keyboard"

        @{b}Keyboard@{ub}

Using this window you can alter how the function keys operate within the program. Each
function key has a default assignment, which you can see by opening the menu.

Additionaly, you can specify which context of help you want to be opened using the HELP
key: program manual (Program) or grammar handbook (Grammar).

@endnode

@node "OptionsTEA" "Teaching Options"

  @{b}Teaching Options@{ub}

 In Teaching Options you can tell eTeacher how to perform exercises.

   @{" Hint                     " link "Hint" 0}
   @{" Auto Repeat              " link "ARepeat" 0}
   @{" Credit after Auto Repeat " link "AutoRCredit" 0}
   @{" Grammar Help in Test     " link "GrHLPTst" 0}
   @{" Intensity level          " link "IntLEVEL" 0}
   @{" Demands Correction       " link "DemCOR" 0}

@endnode

@node "OptionsSND" "Sound and graphics"

  @{b}Sound and graphics options@{ub}

 From this menu you can change the sound effects:

   @{" Sample  Player " link "SndPL" 0}  choose the type of audio player
   @{" Correct Answer " link "SndANSW" 0}  sound reaction for correct answers
   @{" Wrong Answer   " link "SndANSW" 0}  sound reaction for incorrect answers

@endnode

@node "PrgEXP" "Export"

  @{b}Export@{ub}

  With this option you can very easily move all exercises (drill, pictures and samples)
between two computers.  To Export you must choose two directories for exported pictures
and samples, which must be SUBDIRECTORIES of the main directory - for example:
Export/Video and Export/Audio.

  When you enable Export every shown picture and played sample is copied into the
specified directory.  You can also use the "Export" gadget in the editor to export ALL
exercises.

@endnode

@node "OptionsCOM" "Comments"

@{fg shine} @{b}Comments.@{ub}@{fg text}

  Using this option you can modify/create the comment files.  You can choose between
congratulations and invectives.  There are three additional buttons:

   @{b}New@{ub}      create a new comment
   @{b}Delete@{ub}   delete the currently active comment
   @{b}Save@{ub}     save modified comment file
   @{b}Cancel@{ub}   cancel all modifications and exit
   @{b}Ok@{ub}       set comment file but don't save

 Remember that @{b}Save@{ub} only saves changes made to the comment files. If you change a file
with comments, remember to store the settings with @{" Save settings " link "OptionsSVE" 0} from Menu Options.
@endnode

@node "OptionsSVE" "Save settings"

  @{b}Save settings@{ub}

  When you choose this option the current eTeacher configuration will be stored on
disk.  When you run eTeacher again new settings will be loaded and used, otherwise
default settings will be used next time you run eTeacher. Unsaved settings are valid
till you quit eTeacher.

@endnode

@node "OptionsDefault" "Default Settings"

  @{b}Default Settings@{ub}

   Set all system variables to default values.
@endnode

@node "WyborOdpTW" "Choosing answer in Multiple Choice Drill"

  @{b}Choosing answer in Multiple Choice Drill@{ub}

  In multiple choice drills you should choose the correct answer from those available.
Simply click the mouse on the button @{b}A B C D E@{ub} or type the corresponding letter on the
keyboard.  Only ONE answer is correct!

  When clicked, the correct answer will be coloured white. If you gave the incorrect
answer, the selected (incorrect) answer will be coloured red and the correct answer
will be coloured white at the same time.
@endnode

@node "Przyciski" "eTeacher buttons"

  @{b}eTeacher buttons@{ub}

  When you are working with eTeacher you will see a number of buttons. Choose the
button to get more informations:

   @{" Hint             " link "OknoHINT" 0}   hint for current item
   @{" Show All Answers " link "OknoAll" 0}   show all acceptable answers
   @{" Help             " link "OknoHELP" 0}   run internal help
   @{" Instruction      " link "OknoInstr" 0}   give instructions for current drill
   @{" Cancel           " link "OknoCANCEL" 0}   break learning/testing and exit to menu
   @{" Grammar          " link "OknoGRA" 0}   run grammar handbook
   @{" Play             " link "OknoPLAY" 0}   play sound sample
   @{" Pause            " link "OknoPAUSE" 0}    pauses current drill
   @{" Arrow            " link "OknoENT" 0}   go to the next item
@endnode

@node "PrzyciskiED" "Editor buttons"

  @{b}Editor buttons@{ub}

 There are number of buttons in the editor.  Choose the button to get more
informations:

   @{" First    " link "First" 0}   go to the first item
   @{" Previous " link "Prev" 0}   go to the previous item
   @{" Next     " link "Next" 0}   go to the next item
   @{" Last     " link "Last" 0}   go to the last item
   @{" Add      " link "Add" 0}   add new item
   @{" Delete   " link "Delete" 0}   delete current item
   @{" Header   " link "HeaderEdit" 0}   edit header of current exercise
   @{" Help     " link "Help" 0}   help

   @{" OK       " link "OK" 0}   save modified exercise and exit
   @{" Save     " link "Save" 0}   only save
   @{" Cancel   " link "Cancel" 0}   cancel all changes and exit

   @{"?         " link "OknoAll" 0}  prints all DECODED answers (very useful in alternate coding)
@endnode

@node "ScreenInfo" "Informations on the screen"

  @{b}Informations on the screen@{ub}

  On the right side of the screen you will find inforamation about the current
exercise. The right side shows how much of the excercise (in percent) you've already
done, the percent of correct answers and your current score.

  The number (percenage scale) of correct answers depends on your @{" teaching options " link "OptionsTEA" 0},
and can be adjusted depending on your preferences. If you think you're talented
stundent, you can raise it up to the maximium (+10). If you're a novice, you can lower
it.

  While you work with @{" Test Mode " link "Test" 0}, Electronic Teacher displays percent value of items
already done, percent of correct answers and your current score.

  The display in @{" Learn Mode " link "Learn" 0} is limited only to percent of passed items.

In both modes you can see the timer.  The Timer's timing depends on the TICK parameter
in @{" Tooltypes " link "Tooltype" 0}.  Please verify it is correct for your screen mode. For PAL mode
TICK=50, for NTSC TICK=60. But before you change it, verify if it really needs changed.
@endnode

@node "GrammarHelp" "Grammar Help"

  @{b}Grammar Help@{ub}

  eTeacher has its own Grammar Handbook.  It works as an eTeacher Help file, using the
AmigaGuide hypertext system.  You can open the Grammar Handbook in three different
ways:

   1. From the Handbook Menu (by choosing Contents or Index)

   2. Directly from an exercise, by clicking on the "Grammar" button.
      This will cause the Grammar Handbook to be opend on the desired
      page.

   3. By selecting the Grammar Handbook icon from Workbench.
      This way you can use the Grammar Handbook even without
      eTeacher.

@endnode

@node "MenuFCreate" "Menu Project - Create"

    @{b}Menu Project/Create@{ub}

 Using this menu allows you to create a new exercise from scratch.

@endnode

@node "MenuFExit" "Menu Project - Exit"

  @{b}Menu Project - Exit@{ub}

 Ends the current session with eTeacher.

 Note: unsaved program settings will be lost.
@endnode

@node "MFInfo" "About eTeacher"

  @{b}About eTeacher@{ub}

  Opens the About window, displaying information about the program and the publisher.

  Give it a look!

@endnode

@node "MenuFLearn" "Menu Project - Learn"

  @{b}Project Menu - Learn@{ub}

  From this menu you can run any exercise in @{" Learn Mode " link "Learn" 0}. First you must choose the
type of exercise, then choose then its file using the standard Amiga file requester.

@endnode

@node "MenuFTest" "Menu Project - Test"

  @{b}Project Menu - Test@{ub}

  From this menu you can run any exercise in @{" Test Mode " link "Test" 0}. First you must choose the
type of exercise then choose then its file using the standard Amiga file requester.

@endnode

@node "MenuFEdit" "Menu Project - Edit"

  @{b}Project Menu - Edit@{ub}

  Using this menu item you can open and edit any available exercise using eTeacher's
built-in editor.  First you must choose the type of exercise you want to work with and
then load the exercise, then choose its file using the standard Amiga file requester.

@endnode

@node "PrgLAN" "Program Options - Program Language"

  @{b}Program Options - Program Language@{ub}

 This option sets the language used by eTeacher.  After changing this window, texts,
menus and gadgets will use the choosen language.

@endnode

@node "PrgED" "Program Options - Enable Edition"

  @{b}Program Options - Enable Editing@{ub}

When this flag is set, all eTeacher editors will be available (otherwise you can't
modify any exercise).  If you want to avoid any modification just disable this option.

You may also set a @{" Password " link "PrgPASW" 0}. This option is useful when more than one person is using
eTeacher and allows you to avoid "practical jokes" by protecting your data from being
modified.

@endnode

@node "PrgPASW" "Program Options - Password"

  @{b}Program Options - Password@{ub}

  When you want to protect eTeacher files against unwanted modifications use this
option to specify an access password.  If the password is set, eTeacher will ask for it
every time a user tries to enter the Options Menu.

If you disable @{" exercise editing ability " link "PrgED" 0} as well as set a password, nobody will be
able to modify your exercises.

@endnode

@node "SndPL" "Sound Player Type"

  @{b}Sound Player@{ub}

 There are various ways to play @{" sample " link "SoundFile" 0} files:

   1. The internal sound sample player
   2. With any external Shell driven player
   3. By using the DATATYPE system (requires OS3 or better),
   4. With help from the AHI audio system (audio cards mostly)

   Of course, you can also turn the sound off if you so desire.

  - To run eTeacher in INTERNAL mode you don't need any other programs.
    The program reads and plays IFF and WAVE sample files using the
    Amiga's built-in audio hardware.

  - If you want to use a player other than the internal one (e.g. PPC
    optimized sound player), set Sound Player to EXTERNAL. More about
    using external players can be found @{" here " link "ExtPL" 0}.

  - While using the DATATYPE system (it is a part of AmigaOS release 3)
    you must have at least IFF and  WAVE datatypes installed (see the
    "Support" drawer) to play eTeacher samples.

    AHI users: there's special patch for sound.datatype to make it use
               your audio card. Take a look in the "Support" drawer


  If you want to learn quietly, (i.e.  at evenings or nights) just turn the sound OFF.
When sound if off, eTeacher doesn't load any samples, so if you are extremly low on
memory, you can use this option to prevent "Out of memory" problems.

@endnode

@node "SndANSW" "Correct & Wrong Answer."

  @{b}Correct & Incorrect Answer.@{ub}

 You can choose "reaction type" for correct and incorrect answers.  There are five
different choices available:

   Answer       - play answer
   Comment      - play and show comment
   Sound Effect - additional sound effect
   Random       - random effect
   File         - single additional effect file

  When the "Random" option is NOT set, only the additional file is played. If this
option is turned on, eTeacher will play a random effect directly from disk or CD.  All
options are available for both correct and incorrect answers, so you have a lot of
different combinations available.
@endnode

@node "Hint" "Hints"

  @{b}Hints@{ub}

 By turning this option on, you can get hints while in Learn Mode. However, eTeacher
will then ask the question again (even if @{" Intensity Level " link "IntLEVEL" 0} is 1) until it gets the
correct answer without hinting.

@endnode

@node "ARepeat" "Auto Repeat"

  @{b}Auto Repeat@{ub}

 This option works only with @{" Learn Mode " link "Learn" 0}.  If you make a mistake and give an incorrect
answer, eTeacher will ask you the same question again.

@endnode

@node "AutoRCredit" "Credit after Auto Repeat"

  @{b}Credit after Auto Repeat@{ub}

 This option works only in @{" Learn Mode " link "Learn" 0} and when @{" AutoRepeat " link "ARepeat" 0} is enabled. When this
option is on, eTeacher will ask you a question again if your answer is not correct. If
the second answer is correct, eTeacher accepts the second answer as a "good" one and
gives credit for the question's successful completion.

@endnode

@node "GrHLPTst" "Grammar Help in Test"

  @{b}Avaliability of Grammar Help in Test mode@{ub}

 When you turn this option ON, Grammar Help will be available in @{" Test Mode " link "Test" 0} as well.
If the option is OFF, Grammar Help will only be available while in @{" Learn Mode " link "Learn" 0}.

@endnode

@node "IntLEVEL" "Intensity Level"

  @{b}Intensity Level@{ub}

 Intensity level is a numeric value which defines how many attempts a user may make at
the correct answer to a question. Possible values are between 1 and 6. Default is 1,
which means the user has only one try per question.

@endnode

@node "DemCOR" "Demands Correction"

  @{b}Demands Correction@{ub}

 With this option you can change demands while in @{" Test mode " link "Test" 0}. If you think that
eTeacher's notes are too strict or too easy you can correct them. Values between -10 to
+10 are accepted.

@endnode

@node "Wpisywanie" "Typing answers"

  @{b}Typing answers@{ub}

 In all exercises you have to type an answer in the "Your Answer" field. You have to
type all answers very carefully - try to make no errors.  All answers are case
sensitive, and proper punctuation must be used. Press ENTER when finished.

   The field you use when typing in your answer is a standard system string gadget with
all normal editing shortcuts available:

   Backspace  deletes the character to the left side of cursor

   Delete     deletes the character under the cursor and shifts all
              characters to the right of the cursor one space to
              the left.

   Cursor ->  moves the cursor one space to the right

   Cursor <-  moves the cursor one space to the left

   SHIFT  ->  jumps to the end of the line

   SHIFT  <-  jump to the start of the line

   ALT    ->  jumps to the next word

   ALT    <-  jumps to the previous word

   Amiga + X   deletes all text in the gadget

   Amiga + Q   undo

@endnode

@node "OknoHINT" "Hint"

  @{b}Hint@{ub}

  Using this gadget causes the correct answer to appear in the Correct Answer field
list on the screen.  You must retype this answer in the "Your Answer" field to pass the
question.

@{b}
 NOTE:  Even though you retype the hint correctly your answer will be
        accepted but not credited towards the final results.

@endnode

@node "OknoAll" "All correct answers"

  @{b}All correct answers@{ub}

  Using this gadget ALL the correct answers appear in the "Correct Answer" list on the
screen.  You should type one of these answers in the "Your Answer" field to pass the
question.

You shouldn't use this feature very often - it's tough to remember all the correct
answers from the Correct Answer list.

@{b}
  HINT: To close you can click the close window gadget (left upper corner)
        or depress the right mouse button.
@endnode

@node "OknoCW" "Choosing Drills from Window"

  @{b}Choosing Drills from Window@{ub}

   In this window you can choose an exercise from a theme oriented list.

  Available buttons:

  @{b}Learn@{ub}  - run exercise in Learn Mode,

  @{b}Test@{ub}   - run exercise in Test Mode,

  @{b}Add@{ub}    - lets you add any existing exercise to the list,

  @{b}Delete@{ub} - lets you delete any exercise from the list.
                    Deleted exercise is removed only from list -
                    not from disk! You have to save the file to make
                    your changes permanent.

  @{b}Save@{ub}   - lets you save the changed list on disk,

  @{b}Edit@{ub}   - open the exercise to Edit.

@endnode

@node "OknoInstr" "Instruction"

  @{b}Instruction@{ub}

  When you click on this gadget eTeacher will display (and play, if related audio file
is set and available) instructions for the current exercise. Read the instructions
carefully if you are not sure of what to do.

@endnode

@node "OknoENT" "ENTER (arrow)"

  @{b}ENTER (arrow)@{ub}

  Clicking on the big arrow is the same as pressing the ENTER key on the keyboard. When
all items in an exercise are correct, use this arrow to accept it and tell eTeacher
that you are finished with the current item.
@endnode

@node "OknoHELP" "Help"

  @{b}Help@{ub}

 With this button you can get internal eTeacher help.
@endnode

@node "OknoCANCEL" "Cancel"

  @{b}Cancel@{ub}

 When you click on this button the current exercise will be stopped and you can exit to
the Main menu. A confirmation requester will appear first.

@endnode

@node "OknoGRA" "Grammar"

  @{b}Grammar@{ub}

 If this button is active you can open the Grammar Handbook on the desired page.
Grammar Help is available only in @{" Learn Mode " link "Learn" 0} or in Learn and @{" Test Mode " link "Test" 0} depending on
@{" Teaching Options " link "OptionsTEA" 0} in the Options menu.

@endnode

@node "OknoPLAY" "Play"

  @{b}Play@{ub}


  In all drills you can replay any available sound sample by clicking this button.
@endnode

@node "OknoPAUSE" "Pause"

    @{b}Pause@{ub}

  Clicking on the Pause gadget you can stop the current drill. The timer will hold
until you signify you are ready to resume by closing the confirmation requester.
@endnode

@node "Tooltype" "Tooltype description"

  Major functions of eTeacher can be controlled with the preferences editor, but some
can be changed from icon ToolTypes. Here's the list of all the available tooltypes
eTeacher understands.

  NOTE: for almost 99,9% of all cases you do not need to play with the tooltypes!


  Tooltype description (default value is shown in brackets):

   @{b}SCREENMODE@{ub}   - Screenmode for the eTeacher screen     ($8004 for PAL)
                 When you bracket SCREENMODE with () the standard ASL
                 Screen Requester lets you chose the screen mode. The
                 minimum resolution is 640x400.

   @{b}PUBSCRNAME@{ub}   - Name or existing public screen name         (eTeacher)

   @{b}DEPTH@{ub}        - Number of bitplanes to use                  (4)

   @{b}FONT@{ub}         - Font name to use. Here you can change eTeacher's
                 standard font to Cyrylic or another national
                 charset. (eTeacher.font)

   @{b}TICK@{ub}         - refresh rate for desired screenmode         (50)
                 This tooltype is used to manage "speed"
                 of the internal timer in exercises.

   @{b}LANGUAGE1@{ub}    - Name of the language you learn. (ENGLISH)

   @{b}LANGUAGE2@{ub}    - Name of your native language. (POLISH)

   @{b}TMP_DIR@{ub}      - Directory for created temporary files.          (T:)
                 If you have a lot of memory simply use T:.
                 If you havn't - try using a harddisk directory.

   @{b}REQ_X@{ub}        - X position of ASL Requester
   @{b}REQ_Y@{ub}        - Y
   @{b}REQ_W@{ub}        - width
   @{b}REQ_H@{ub}        - height

   @{b}DEF_GRA@{ub}      - Default Congratulation file (CommentsEnglish.GRA)
                           If there is no configuration file stored on harddisk
                           eTeacher will use THIS congratulation file.

   @{b}DEF_INV@{ub}      - Default Invective file (CommentsEnglis.INV)

   @{b}ALT_LANGUAGE@{ub} - Alternative language.
        If you set this tooltype then eTeacher always will start with your national
        language. Otherwise eTeacher will start with saved settings or in English.

   @{b}WINPATERN@{ub}    - Window pattern file
        If you working wit at least 32 colours then you are able to use window
        patterns. This option works only in LEARN and TEST mode. File pattern must
        be an IFF file wit 8 or 16 colours depth. You have to store them in DATA
        directory. To avoid colour collision problems (multimedia drill) you should
        use colours 8-15.
@endnode

@node "Thumbnails" "Thumbnails"

    @{b}Thumbnails@{ub}

You can use all pictures stored on CD-ROM. To start browsing CD pictures click on
CD-gadget in Options/Graphics or in Edit/Create Mode. If you are using "Try multicolor
first" option colour depth will be depend on screen depth. Otherwise all pictures will
be in 16 colours.

Inside the CD-browse window you can use additional keys:

   up         - move highlighting one item up   (show previous picture)
   down       -                   one item down (show next picture)
   SHIFT+up   -                   ten items up
   SHIFT+down -                   ten items down
   CTRL +up   -                   to first item (show first picture)
   CTRL +down -                   to last  item (show last picture)
   A..Z       -                   to first picture starts with choosen letter
   ESC        - exit from CD-browser without choosing picture
   ENTER      -                      with choosen picture
@endnode

@node "CDbrowser" "CD-sample browser"

    @{b}CD-sample browser@{ub}

You can use all samples stored on CD-ROM. To start browsing CD samples click on
CD-gadget in Edit/Create Mode, Option/Comments or Options/Sound window. All samples are
divided to seven groups:

   1.Words           (different words)
   2.Samples         (additional samples)
   3.Drills          (drill samples)
   4.Instructions    (drill instructions)
   5.Informations    (different informations)
   6.Congratulations
   7.Invectives

When you choose desired group list contents will be updated. Clicking on each item of
the list you will hear the sample. Press OK gadget to accept choosen item.
@endnode

